00:54:52.978 --> 00:54:56.838
and others don't, then that makes it very difficult,

909
00:54:57.248 --> 00:54:59.898
uh, for patients, you know, who are not in

910
00:54:59.958 --> 00:55:03.818
the catchment area of Children's Hospital of Philadelphia to access

911
00:55:03.878 --> 00:55:07.858
that therapy. There's also, of course, the fact that you can scale

912
00:55:07.958 --> 00:55:11.848
CAR T-cells, um, but it is a lot of work and it still does cost a lot of

913
00:55:11.878 --> 00:55:15.838
money. So I'd love to hear just your thoughts on, you know, imagine a world

914
00:55:15.938 --> 00:55:19.390
if we, you know-took this idea to

915
00:55:19.450 --> 00:55:23.350
its logical conclusion. And then also how is it, for example,

916
00:55:23.370 --> 00:55:26.190
at CHOP, that you're sustaining that infrastructure?

917
00:55:26.310 --> 00:55:30.210
Could CHOP be a CAR T-cell factory, but for the

918
00:55:30.230 --> 00:55:34.130
Philadelphia area? And is the funding for

919
00:55:34.190 --> 00:55:34.370
that

920
00:55:35.250 --> 00:55:39.210
going to be sustainable? Are you able to have the institutional commitment to make

921
00:55:39.220 --> 00:55:41.870
those products available for years to come?

922
00:55:42.010 --> 00:55:43.470
I know you're not speaking on behalf of CHOP.

923
00:55:43.950 --> 00:55:47.160
Yeah. Thank you for the question. Yeah, I certainly can't speak on behalf of

